# n8n Node Structure

n8n nodes follow a specific structure to integrate with the n8n platform. This project follows standard n8n community node patterns.

## Node Architecture

Each node in n8n consists of several key files:

1. **Main Node File (`*.node.ts`)** - Contains the node class implementation with:
   - Node definition and metadata
   - `execute()` or `trigger()` methods to run the node's functionality

2. **Node Options File (`*.node.options.ts`)** - Contains the node's UI option definitions:
   - Parameters
   - Input fields
   - Option types
   - Default values

3. **Node Metadata File (`*.node.json`)** - Contains node display information:
   - Name
   - Color
   - Icon
   - Description

## Discord Nodes Structure

This package contains two main nodes:

- **Discord Send Node**:
  - [Discord.node.ts](mdc:src/nodes/Discord/Discord.node.ts) - Main implementation
  - [Discord.node.options.ts](mdc:src/nodes/Discord/Discord.node.options.ts) - UI options
  - [Discord.node.json](mdc:src/nodes/Discord/Discord.node.json) - Node metadata

- **Discord Trigger Node**:
  - [DiscordTrigger.node.ts](mdc:src/nodes/Discord/DiscordTrigger.node.ts) - Main implementation
  - [DiscordTrigger.node.options.ts](mdc:src/nodes/Discord/DiscordTrigger.node.options.ts) - UI options
  - [DiscordTrigger.node.json](mdc:src/nodes/Discord/DiscordTrigger.node.json) - Node metadata

